he was like, "Shin Young disappointed me today."

472
00:15:14,486 --> 00:15:15,526
"Don't let her do it."

473
00:15:17,426 --> 00:15:19,596
"Now let's hear from Tei!" That's what he was like.

474
00:15:20,526 --> 00:15:21,725
"Now let's hear from Tei."

475
00:15:21,726 --> 00:15:23,365
- I would be upset.
- He moved on right away.

476
00:15:23,366 --> 00:15:24,495
- He moved on right away.
- Exactly.

477
00:15:24,496 --> 00:15:25,496
- "Don't let her do it."
- Right.

478
00:15:25,497 --> 00:15:27,635
- "Don't let her do it."
- A pro must always be prepared.

479
00:15:27,636 --> 00:15:29,536
I'm at 100 percent again. I'm feeling 100 percent again.

480
00:15:30,776 --> 00:15:31,905
- You're a genius.
- I'm feeling 100 percent.

481
00:15:31,906 --> 00:15:34,905
- It was obvious she wasn't ready.
- You must do it somehow.

482
00:15:34,906 --> 00:15:35,975
She did it right away.

483
00:15:35,976 --> 00:15:37,545
- I knew it because she's my friend.
- She did it right away.

484
00:15:37,546 --> 00:15:39,145
- You must not let him down.
- She's amazing.

485
00:15:39,146 --> 00:15:40,686
- She's incredible.
- He'd give you this look.

486
00:15:40,846 --> 00:15:42,015
"I'm disappointed."

487
00:15:42,016 --> 00:15:44,355
Shin Young is called Shin D at Noon as a radio DJ.

488
00:15:44,356 --> 00:15:46,385
- Tei is called Good Morning Tei D.
- "Tei D?"

489
00:15:46,386 --> 00:15:47,556
- Because of my radio show.
- "Tei D?"

490
00:15:47,656 --> 00:15:48,985
I'm called Tei D because I'm DJ Tei.

491
00:15:48,986 --> 00:15:50,525
- Oh, I see.
- I'm called Shin D...

492
00:15:50,526 --> 00:15:52,625
as I'm DJ Shin Young. He's Tei D as he's DJ Tei.

493
00:15:52,626 --> 00:15:54,196
- We're Shin D and Tei D.
- Tei D.

494
00:15:54,526 --> 00:15:55,626
What about you, Yeong Cheol?

495
00:15:55,766 --> 00:15:57,095
I'm called Cherup D.

496
00:15:57,096 --> 00:15:59,306
- Cherup D.
- Who gave you that name?

497
00:15:59,706 --> 00:16:00,835
The listeners of my show did.

498
00:16:00,836 --> 00:16:03,636
- It means that I cheer them up.
- I see.

499
00:16:04,106 --> 00:16:05,776
It also sounds similar to the word "immature," which describes me.

500
00:16:06,106 --> 00:16:07,645
So they call me Cherup D.

501
00:16:07,646 --> 00:16:09,175
What do you call the listeners of your radio show?

502
00:16:09,176 --> 00:16:12,446
- We call our fans "elves."
- They have a nickname.

503
00:16:12,886 --> 00:16:13,946
I call them "teachers."

504
00:16:14,486 --> 00:16:16,656
I'm a bit short on general knowledge.

505
00:16:16,886 --> 00:16:18,686
- That's amazing.
- One time, during my show,

506
00:16:18,886 --> 00:16:20,956
I was supposed to say "the Galapagos Islands."

507
00:16:21,286 --> 00:16:23,195
It's the home of sea turtles.

508
00:16:23,196 --> 00:16:25,796
I didn't know that's what it meant. I thought it meant "mister."

509
00:16:25,966 --> 00:16:28,926
I said, "Right. Mr. Galapagos must have his own struggles."

510
00:16:29,896 --> 00:16:31,435
- My goodness.
- I said that because I didn't know.

511
00:16:31,436 --> 00:16:32,465
You thought it was someone's name.

512
00:16:32,466 --> 00:16:33,805
I thought it was a title like "Ms."

513
00:16:33,806 --> 00:16:34,966
- Ms. Heebab.
- "Ms. Heebab."

514
00:16:35,206 --> 00:16:36,805
- Mr. Ha Bin. I thought that was it.
- That's understandable.

515
00:16:36,806 --> 00:16:37,975
You thought it was the name of a foreigner?

516
00:16:37,976 --> 00:16:39,576
- "Mr. Galapagos also..."
- It sounds like a foreign name.

517
00:16:39,776 --> 00:16:42,176
And that was it. I didn't know what to say after that.

518
00:16:42,376 --> 00:16:45,176
I feel like I learn a new life lesson every day.

519
00:16:45,376 --> 00:16:48,215
- That's why I call them "teachers."
- "Teachers." I see.

520
00:16:48,216 --> 00:16:49,555
- That's great.
- That's meaningful.

521
00:16:49,556 --> 00:16:50,816
- What about you, Tei?
- They're like your mentors.

522
00:16:50,956 --> 00:16:54,126
- My listeners gave me a nickname.
- What is it?

523
00:16:54,456 --> 00:16:55,855
- It's TB.
- "TB?"

524
00:16:55,856 --> 00:16:57,196
- What does it mean?
- Tei Boomer?

525
00:16:57,356 --> 00:16:58,655
- I didn't know I was a boomer.
- You are?

526
00:16:58,656 --> 00:16:59,995
- Like "Boomer Dae Hee?"
- Are you a boomer?

527
00:16:59,996 --> 00:17:01,295
- I don't think you are.
- I was surprised to know that.

528
00:17:01,296 --> 00:17:03,395
But come to think of it, when I was in school,

529
00:17:03,396 --> 00:17:05,196
I was always the head of the student guidance club.

530
00:17:06,106 --> 00:17:08,136
I guess that side of me comes out since I host the show every day.

531
00:17:08,906 --> 00:17:10,736
As I keep making such comments...

532
00:17:10,906 --> 00:17:14,346
What are the examples of comments that make you sound like a boomer?

533
00:17:14,476 --> 00:17:16,046
I'm supposed to say only cheerful words.

534
00:17:16,316 --> 00:17:18,675
- When someone says he's tired...
- Oh, you give them sharp advice.

535
00:17:18,676 --> 00:17:21,285
Right. I'm too straightforward when I give them advice.

536
00:17:21,286 --> 00:17:22,315
Can you give us an example?

537
00:17:22,316 --> 00:17:23,815
Someone said, "I change jobs frequently,"

538
00:17:23,816 --> 00:17:26,886
- "which is very stressful."
- A listener shared his story.

539
00:17:27,026 --> 00:17:30,155
- I asked how often he changed it.
- Right.

540
00:17:30,156 --> 00:17:32,056
He said he changed jobs every three months.

541
00:17:32,996 --> 00:17:34,696
I said that the problem might lie within him.

542
00:17:35,466 --> 00:17:37,665
(Shocked)

543
00:17:37,666 --> 00:17:40,365
People share their stories seeking empathy.

544
00:17:40,366 --> 00:17:41,765
- But...
- I empathize with them too.

545
00:17:41,766 --> 00:17:43,106
We empathize with their struggles too.

546
00:17:43,576 --> 00:17:45,106
Both he and I are the thinking type.

547
00:17:45,276 --> 00:17:47,706
Sometimes listeners say, "I really want to quit my job."

548
00:17:48,076 --> 00:17:50,276
"I'll just pack up and vanish." Then I'm supposed to say,

549
00:17:50,446 --> 00:17:52,985
"It must be stressful, but hold out until the weekend."

550
00:17:52,986 --> 00:17:55,646
"How about you go on a trip every weekend?"

551
00:17:55,786 --> 00:17:57,085
This is the standard answer.

552
00:17:57,086 --> 00:17:58,115
Hearing that alone makes me feel uncomfortable.

553
00:17:58,116 --> 00:17:59,786
It's the standard answer, but I would say,

554
00:17:59,926 --> 00:18:01,356
"You have to bite the bullet."

555
00:18:01,926 --> 00:18:03,356
"Keep it together."

556
00:18:03,526 --> 00:18:05,755
"If you have children, you have to really tough it out."

557
00:18:05,756 --> 00:18:07,466
- I would say the same thing.
- "Do you understand?"

558
00:18:07,566 --> 00:18:09,465
- That's a realistic answer.
- I'd say, "Stop complaining..."

559
00:18:09,466 --> 00:18:10,795
- Absolutely.
- "and suck it up."

560
00:18:10,796 --> 00:18:12,536
- You're doing a great job.
- The best achievement.

561
00:18:12,666 --> 00:18:13,706
- Really?
- Yes.

562
00:18:14,336 --> 00:18:16,535
- He's a total thinker.
- He's the best thinker.

563
00:18:16,536 --> 00:18:17,735
- He's the king of thinkers.
- The king of thinkers.

564
00:18:17,736 --> 00:18:18,975
- Right.
- You should advise them sternly.

565
00:18:18,976 --> 00:18:21,175
- We should do that, you know.
- He must be wearing a thong too.

566
00:18:21,176 --> 00:18:24,215
- They need diverse points of view.
- That's right.

567
00:18:24,216 --> 00:18:25,816
- I agree.
- Hee Chul was a radio DJ too, yes?

568
00:18:25,916 --> 00:18:28,345
- I was a radio DJ a long time ago.
- Right.

569
00:18:28,346 --> 00:18:29,485
He hosted "Young Street."

570
00:18:29,486 --> 00:18:31,056
- I was a little...
- For how many years did he host it?

571
00:18:31,386 --> 00:18:32,586
I was a bit arrogant.

572
00:18:32,826 --> 00:18:34,225
I said, "Since I'm a flower,"

573
00:18:34,226 --> 00:18:36,696
"I'll call you flower petals."

574
00:18:37,856 --> 00:18:39,496
- He has an excessively huge ego.
- Really?

575
00:18:39,626 --> 00:18:41,566
- My gosh. Seriously...
- It's possible only for Hee Chul.

576
00:18:41,626 --> 00:18:43,265
Right. But to me, hosting a radio show...

577
00:18:43,266 --> 00:18:45,366
"Young Street" started airing at 8pm.

578
00:18:45,736 --> 00:18:47,505
- How nice.
- So I always said things like,

579
00:18:47,506 --> 00:18:49,275
"No dozing off at the wheel even in heavy traffic."

580
00:18:49,276 --> 00:18:51,675
"Everyone except for those who are driving, put your hands up."

581
00:18:51,676 --> 00:18:52,805
- I always said such things.
- I see.

582
00:18:52,806 --> 00:18:54,245
The vibes of radio shows are different...

583
00:18:54,246 --> 00:18:55,676
- depending on the time slot.
- That's right.

584
00:18:56,016 --> 00:18:58,446
- Tei, how do you speak?
- During Tei's show...

585
00:18:58,646 --> 00:19:02,186
I started my career as a radio DJ at KBS, following Kim Dong Ryul.

586
00:19:02,316 --> 00:19:04,356
- That sounds romantic.
- It was called "Music Island."

587
00:19:04,886 --> 00:19:06,025
- I hosted the night show...
- It suits you.

588
00:19:06,026 --> 00:19:07,525
- for over two years.
- Right.

589
00:19:07,526 --> 00:19:09,826
- I spoke very calmly back then.
- Quietly.

590
00:19:10,056 --> 00:19:11,456
Right before signing off...

591
00:19:12,156 --> 00:19:14,565
Since Sung Si Kyung's signature comment was so iconic...

592
00:19:14,566 --> 00:19:16,465
- "Sleep well."
- Yes, because it was so iconic,

593
00:19:16,466 --> 00:19:18,095
- His show aired in the same slot.
- I had to come up with my own.

594
00:19:18,096 --> 00:19:20,266
- "Sleep well."
- I went too far with it.

595
00:19:20,436 --> 00:19:22,036
- So I got scolded harshly.
- What did you say?

596
00:19:22,266 --> 00:19:23,335
- I said, - Yes?

597
00:19:23,336 --> 00:19:25,675
"I hope you all wrap up your day beautifully."

598
00:19:25,676 --> 00:19:27,446
"I will dream about you."

599
00:19:28,576 --> 00:19:31,315
- That's a bit...
- You've changed.

600
00:19:31,316 --> 00:19:34,016
Get much better sleep than REM sleep. I love you.

601
00:19:34,716 --> 00:19:36,455
What about in the morning?

602
00:19:36,456 --> 00:19:37,785
- Mornings...
- Mornings have to be energetic.

603
00:19:37,786 --> 00:19:39,255
- Of course.
- Energetic?

604
00:19:39,256 --> 00:19:41,885
- Really?
- With my most energetic voice,

605
00:19:41,886 --> 00:19:43,825
- I...
- "Good morning, this is Tei!"

606
00:19:43,826 --> 00:19:44,925
For real?

607
00:19:44,926 --> 00:19:45,926
- Nice.
- That's very energetic.

608
00:19:45,927 --> 00:19:47,525
"Have a good Tei!"

609
00:19:47,526 --> 00:19:49,165
- He sounds like that on the radio.
- Right?

610
00:19:49,166 --> 00:19:51,096
- What about at noon?
- Noon, Shin Young?

611
00:19:51,136 --> 00:19:52,136
As for "Hope Song at Noon,"

612
00:19:52,137 --> 00:19:53,965
"'Hope Song at Noon, ' this is Kim Shin Young!"

613
00:19:53,966 --> 00:19:55,435
- Like so.
- How bright.

614
00:19:55,436 --> 00:19:56,875
- Yes, I must be bright.
- Cool.

615
00:19:56,876 --> 00:19:59,076
- "Hope Song at Noon."
- I've heard...

616
00:19:59,236 --> 00:20:01,345
- that opening a thousand times.
- Totally.

617
00:20:01,346 --> 00:20:03,375
- I must sound bright.
- Of course.

618
00:20:03,376 --> 00:20:06,685
At around 12:40pm,

619
00:20:06,686 --> 00:20:08,485
our radio becomes "Shin Young's Club."

620
00:20:08,486 --> 00:20:09,885
We must make people hyper.

621
00:20:09,886 --> 00:20:11,916
- People feel drowsy after lunch.
- The drowsiness.

622
00:20:12,186 --> 00:20:14,455
"Okie dokie, Macintosh, Ida Daussy, Namyangju,"

623
00:20:14,456 --> 00:20:15,685
"the honorary ambassador," this is Kim Shin Young!"

624
00:20:15,686 --> 00:20:16,925
- "Let's go!"
- What?

625
00:20:16,926 --> 00:20:18,626
- Wait.
- "Show!"

626
00:20:18,726 --> 00:20:20,066
- What was after "Okie dokie?"
- "Okie dokie."

627
00:20:20,096 --> 00:20:22,525
"Okie dokie, Macintosh, Ida Daussy, Namyangju,"

628
00:20:22,526 --> 00:20:24,536
"Namyangju's honorary ambassador, this is Kim Shin Young!"

629
00:20:24,996 --> 00:20:26,065
- Amazing.
- Macintosh?

630
00:20:26,066 --> 00:20:28,535
- There was a city.
- I've said that for five years...

631
00:20:28,536 --> 00:20:30,806
and actually became the honorary ambassador of Namyangju.

632
00:20:31,336 --> 00:20:32,375
Your dream came true.

633
00:20:32,376 --> 00:20:33,645
- Thanks to the introduction?
- I've never lived there.

634
00:20:33,646 --> 00:20:35,545
- Yes.
- She's never lived in Namyangju.

635
00:20:35,546 --> 00:20:36,945
No, I've never lived in Namyangju.

636
00:20:36,946 --> 00:20:39,515
What's worse, Ida Daussy actually lives in Namyangju,

637
00:20:39,516 --> 00:20:41,046
but isn't the honorary ambassador.

638
00:20:41,486 --> 00:20:42,646
I feel terrible about it.

639
00:20:43,186 --> 00:20:44,316
I really do.

640
00:20:44,886 --> 00:20:47,456
- Ida Daussy and Namyangju.
- I constantly wake people up.

641
00:20:47,726 --> 00:20:50,096
"Wake up! Come on!"

642
00:20:50,226 --> 00:20:53,025
"Go! Turn left!"

643
00:20:53,026 --> 00:20:55,165
- "Turn right!" That's what I do.
- Right.

644
00:20:55,166 --> 00:20:57,165
Just like Kang Ho Dong used to wake people up.

645
00:20:57,166 --> 00:20:58,995
- After all, he's my teacher.
- Shin Young.

646
00:20:58,996 --> 00:21:01,005
Back when you did the radio with Shin Dong at night.

647
00:21:01,006 --> 00:21:02,435
- "SimSimTaPa."
- How did you sound?

648
00:21:02,436 --> 00:21:03,575
- At midnight.
- Back then?

649
00:21:03,576 --> 00:21:06,205
"Shin Dong and Kim Shin Young's 'SimSimTaPa!'"

650
00:21:06,206 --> 00:21:07,945
- That was our introduction.
- The time doesn't matter.

651
00:21:07,946 --> 00:21:09,515
- No, it doesn't.
- I know, right?

652
00:21:09,516 --> 00:21:12,815
But I have a time slot I'm dying to be on the radio.

653
00:21:12,816 --> 00:21:14,885
- What time?
- At 10pm and such.

654
00:21:14,886 --> 00:21:16,315
- That mellow time.
- Jeong Ji Yeong...

655
00:21:16,316 --> 00:21:18,315
- Yes, that mellow time.
- Right.

656
00:21:18,316 --> 00:21:20,656
"Yes, that's right."

657
00:21:20,826 --> 00:21:22,355
- "I agree."
- How calm.

658
00:21:22,356 --> 00:21:24,295
"Here are two songs."

659
00:21:24,296 --> 00:21:26,125
- That's how she hosts the show.
- Her voice is soothing.

660
00:21:26,126 --> 00:21:29,266
What if Lee Gye In were to host "Hope Song at Noon?"

661
00:21:29,496 --> 00:21:34,606
"'Hope Song at Noon, ' this is Kim Shin Young!"

662
00:21:35,066 --> 00:21:37,535
- Ho Dong is so mean.
- Happy now?

663
00:21:37,536 --> 00:21:40,345
- Okay?
- You're in great condition.

664
00:21:40,346 --> 00:21:42,005
- Do you feel proud?
- Amazing.

665
00:21:42,006 --> 00:21:43,245
- Ho Dong was being mean.
- Right?

666
00:21:43,246 --> 00:21:45,175
- Seriously.
- I thought we were on "Star King."

667
00:21:45,176 --> 00:21:47,285
What's with your persistence?

668
00:21:47,286 --> 00:21:50,516
- Unbelievable.
- If Ho Dong likes something,

669
00:21:50,856 --> 00:21:52,415
- he makes people do it repeatedly.
- Exactly.

670
00:21:52,416 --> 00:21:54,325
If you think about it, during "Star King..."

671
00:21:54,326 --> 00:21:56,456
- Don't you want to see that again?
- During "Star King,"

672
00:21:56,826 --> 00:21:57,955
Ho Dong did nothing.

673
00:21:57,956 --> 00:21:59,095
- No.
- It was up to us.

674
00:21:59,096 --> 00:22:00,925
- I know.
- He just made people do things.

675
00:22:00,926 --> 00:22:02,465
Even though I can't somersault,

676
00:22:02,466 --> 00:22:04,066
he's like, "No, you totally can!"

677
00:22:05,066 --> 00:22:07,035
- "Stop lying!"
- Exactly.

678
00:22:07,036 --> 00:22:08,935
- "Stop lying!"
- You have to do it.

679
00:22:08,936 --> 00:22:11,476
"Everyone, you'll be shocked by what I'm about to tell you!"

680
00:22:11,636 --> 00:22:12,776
"Andy..."

681
00:22:14,876 --> 00:22:16,006
"of SHINHWA..."

682
00:22:16,246 --> 00:22:17,715
"will dance right now!"

683
00:22:17,716 --> 00:22:18,916
But Andy had no idea about it.

684
00:22:21,546 --> 00:22:23,055
- "What?"
- And he had to dance.

685
00:22:23,056 --> 00:22:24,555
(Me? Is this okay?)

686
00:22:24,556 --> 00:22:25,615
He had to do it,

687
00:22:25,616 --> 00:22:26,885
- no questions asked.
- Exactly.

688
00:22:26,886 --> 00:22:28,455
I'm telling you he's a magician.

689
00:22:28,456 --> 00:22:29,655
And if Andy messed up...

690
00:22:29,656 --> 00:22:31,495
Shin Young, this is the perfect time for a somersault.

691
00:22:31,496 --> 00:22:33,126
But I can't do it.

692
00:22:33,266 --> 00:22:35,096
- Stop lying!
- "Stop lying!"

693
00:22:36,096 --> 00:22:37,165
That's right.

694
00:22:37,166 --> 00:22:39,366
"Writer, don't make Shin Young do it."

695
00:22:40,166 --> 00:22:42,766
"Everyone, you'll be shocked by what I'm about to tell you!"

696
00:22:42,836 --> 00:22:46,035
"Our eardrums are already excited."

697
00:22:46,036 --> 00:22:47,846
"Tei, sing us a song!"

698
00:22:49,406 --> 00:22:51,546
(The vending machine sings a song.)

699
00:22:51,776 --> 00:22:53,716
"Tei, you're in great condition!"

700
00:22:54,186 --> 00:22:56,046
"Nice one, Tei. Good, Tei."

701
00:22:56,256 --> 00:22:58,556
- Ho Dong has rapid mood swings.
- Totally.

702
00:22:58,786 --> 00:23:01,255
Ho Dong does nothing. He makes people do things.

703
00:23:01,256 --> 00:23:02,425
- Exactly.
- Here's what's different...

704
00:23:02,426 --> 00:23:03,595
about Shin Young.

705
00:23:03,596 --> 00:23:05,095
People normally sit still.

706
00:23:05,096 --> 00:23:07,666
As for Shin Young, her feet are moving to jump out when asked.

707
00:23:07,796 --> 00:23:09,526
Her feet are always moving.

708
00:23:10,066 --> 00:23:12,866
- I keep myself prepared.
- Back to the topic of the radio,

709
00:23:12,936 --> 00:23:14,165
- it's live, right?
- Yes.

710
00:23:14,166 --> 00:23:16,876
What was the biggest mistake you made?

711
00:23:17,206 --> 00:23:19,036
The biggest mistake I made.

712
00:23:19,536 --> 00:23:22,675
"We'll listen to 'Song Request ' by Lee So Ra in the Top Ten."

713
00:23:22,676 --> 00:23:23,715
- Things like that.
- Right.

714
00:23:23,716 --> 00:23:25,446
- The requested songs.
- Yes.

715
00:23:25,616 --> 00:23:27,945
It was "Lee So Ra in the Top Ten." But too tired,

716
00:23:27,946 --> 00:23:29,416
I said, "Top Ten So Ra."

717
00:23:30,316 --> 00:23:31,585
At times, we forget words.

718
00:23:31,586 --> 00:23:33,185
- Exactly.
- We combine words.

719
00:23:33,186 --> 00:23:34,485
- "Here's..."
- Top Ten So Ra.

720
00:23:34,486 --> 00:23:36,226
"'Song Request' by Top Ten So Ra!"

721
00:23:36,796 --> 00:23:38,555
- "This is bad."
- The show...

722
00:23:38,556 --> 00:23:40,265
- That was bad.
- And...

723
00:23:40,266 --> 00:23:42,265
- The pronunciation and such.
- Yes.

724
00:23:42,266 --> 00:23:45,465
During "Shin Dong and Kim Shin Young's SimSimTaPa,"

725
00:23:45,466 --> 00:23:47,236
Shin Dong and I had to read a letter.

726
00:23:47,636 --> 00:23:50,676
It was about a heartbreaking moment.

727
00:23:50,706 --> 00:23:54,676
The last bit said, "Everything was a prank."

728
00:23:55,046 --> 00:23:57,775
To change up the mood...

729
00:23:57,776 --> 00:24:00,786
