730
00:24:00,846 --> 00:24:03,786
"Everything was a prank!"

731
00:24:04,386 --> 00:24:07,886
- "Or so I was hoping."
- What? I don't get it.

732
00:24:08,726 --> 00:24:10,655
- Was it not a prank?
- The spacing was wrong.

733
00:24:10,656 --> 00:24:12,155
- It was on the next page.
- The letter itself...

734
00:24:12,156 --> 00:24:13,665
was heartbreaking.

735
00:24:13,666 --> 00:24:15,595
- A tough moment.
- Yes,

736
00:24:15,596 --> 00:24:17,965
but Shin Dong thought it was a prank...

737
00:24:17,966 --> 00:24:21,966
and read it out like, "Everything was a prank!"

738
00:24:23,076 --> 00:24:26,546
- "Or so I was hoping."
- That's a skit right there.

739
00:24:26,746 --> 00:24:28,645
- "That was how hard it was."
- He handled it well...

740
00:24:28,646 --> 00:24:30,215
- with wit.
- Really.

741
00:24:30,216 --> 00:24:31,345
- I got all nervous.
- Shin Dong had it tough too.

742
00:24:31,346 --> 00:24:33,245
- Things like that.
- I doubt Tei makes mistakes.

743
00:24:33,246 --> 00:24:36,085
- I rarely make mistakes.
- Right.

744
00:24:36,086 --> 00:24:37,685
But during the mornings,

745
00:24:37,686 --> 00:24:39,285
- because of traffic, - Right.

746
00:24:39,286 --> 00:24:41,725
I was on the verge of being late many times in the beginning.

747
00:24:41,726 --> 00:24:43,325
- That's bad.
- The thing is,

748
00:24:43,326 --> 00:24:44,955
I wasn't 10 or 20 minutes late.

749
00:24:44,956 --> 00:24:46,365
- I was 40 minutes late.
- For real?

750
00:24:46,366 --> 00:24:47,525
- That's a huge screw-up.
- Oh, no.

751
00:24:47,526 --> 00:24:48,725
- That's bad.
- It's scary. The radio is live.

752
00:24:48,726 --> 00:24:49,735
- How do you handle it?
- Seriously.

753
00:24:49,736 --> 00:24:50,765
- In such situations...
- What do you do?

754
00:24:50,766 --> 00:24:53,006
Fortunately, some announcers...

755
00:24:53,306 --> 00:24:54,935
are at the company at dawn.

756
00:24:54,936 --> 00:24:56,035
(The dawn announcers fill in.)

757
00:24:56,036 --> 00:24:57,105
They'd be woken up...

758
00:24:57,106 --> 00:24:58,206
- and rush down...
- Right.

759
00:24:58,406 --> 00:25:00,205
To do the introduction. I'd arrive by then.

760
00:25:00,206 --> 00:25:02,446
- Those were my mistakes.
- Were you late?

761
00:25:02,506 --> 00:25:04,175
- I was late in the beginning.
- In the beginning.

762
00:25:04,176 --> 00:25:05,245
About two times.

763
00:25:05,246 --> 00:25:07,285
- What about you, Yeong Cheol?
- I was never late.

764
00:25:07,286 --> 00:25:08,345
- Not even once?
- You see...

765
00:25:08,346 --> 00:25:11,356
Shin Young, Yeong Cheol just asked because he was never late.

766
00:25:11,456 --> 00:25:13,326
- To be asked back.
- No wonder he's in first place.

767
00:25:13,926 --> 00:25:15,026
Yeong Cheol...

768
00:25:15,086 --> 00:25:16,856
First place is indeed different.

769
00:25:17,196 --> 00:25:18,695
- Did you see his face just now?
- Yeong Cheol...

770
00:25:18,696 --> 00:25:21,226
I had to do the introduction over the phone because of an accident...

771
00:25:21,296 --> 00:25:23,265
- near Jamsu Bridge.
- Is that so?

772
00:25:23,266 --> 00:25:24,835
Honestly,

773
00:25:24,836 --> 00:25:26,535
I sometimes find this show challenging,

774
00:25:26,536 --> 00:25:28,235
even though it's only once a week.

775
00:25:28,236 --> 00:25:29,365
He finds it really tough.

776
00:25:29,366 --> 00:25:31,035
- I can tell.
- But radio shows...

777
00:25:31,036 --> 00:25:32,435
- are on every day.
- Yes.

778
00:25:32,436 --> 00:25:33,845
- Isn't it tough?
- You must be diligent.

779
00:25:33,846 --> 00:25:36,545
We host the radio with a sense of responsibility every day.

780
00:25:36,546 --> 00:25:37,975
- Of course.
- People wait for me...

781
00:25:37,976 --> 00:25:39,545
- and for that exact show.
- That's a sense of responsibility.

782
00:25:39,546 --> 00:25:42,015
- You've got fans too.
- I'm like an anonymous...

783
00:25:42,016 --> 00:25:43,786
- confession board for those...
- Right.

784
00:25:43,956 --> 00:25:46,186
Who are lonely, having a hard time, or can't talk to anyone.

785
00:25:46,756 --> 00:25:48,225
- Nice.
- That sense of responsibility...

786
00:25:48,226 --> 00:25:49,685
makes me host the show every day.

787
00:25:49,686 --> 00:25:52,155
As for me, I host the morning show, which feels different.

788
00:25:52,156 --> 00:25:53,865
I didn't know what it was like in the afternoon or evening.

789
00:25:53,866 --> 00:25:56,595
Every morning, I dread hosting the radio.

790
00:25:56,596 --> 00:25:57,995
- It's really tough.
- For real.

791
00:25:57,996 --> 00:25:59,235
It's incredibly tough.

792
00:25:59,236 --> 00:26:00,705
The morning radio feels like...

793
00:26:00,706 --> 00:26:02,805
a training ground for my sincerity as an adult.

794
00:26:02,806 --> 00:26:03,835
I agree.

795
00:26:03,836 --> 00:26:05,235
I reflect on myself every morning.

796
00:26:05,236 --> 00:26:07,645
The moment I leave my house,

797
00:26:07,646 --> 00:26:09,445
the world is already in full motion.

798
00:26:09,446 --> 00:26:11,015
While waiting,

799
00:26:11,016 --> 00:26:14,446
many listeners greet me in the online chatroom.

800
00:26:14,786 --> 00:26:15,815
That makes me...

801
00:26:15,816 --> 00:26:17,855
- Right.
- want to live diligently.

802
00:26:17,856 --> 00:26:19,485
You must keep the night before free.

803
00:26:19,486 --> 00:26:21,925
- Yes, it's a must.
- What about you, Yeong Cheol?

804
00:26:21,926 --> 00:26:23,495
- In the morning.
- Yeong Cheol gets excited.

805
00:26:23,496 --> 00:26:24,755
- Right?
- How are you in the mornings?

806
00:26:24,756 --> 00:26:26,925
I grew up listening to the radio.

807
00:26:26,926 --> 00:26:28,365
- Right.
- I had sent a letter to a show,

808
00:26:28,366 --> 00:26:29,936
and my name was read out loud.

809
00:26:30,466 --> 00:26:32,896
- He's a real radio lover.
- So when I read a letter,

810
00:26:33,166 --> 00:26:35,765
I do it with passion, like when my name...

811
00:26:35,766 --> 00:26:38,475
was read out loud as a teenager.

812
00:26:38,476 --> 00:26:39,875
But no matter...

813
00:26:39,876 --> 00:26:41,376
- how good a DJ you are, - Yes?

814
00:26:41,406 --> 00:26:43,245
There must be moments when a guest...

815
00:26:43,246 --> 00:26:45,076
- gives you a hard time.
- Totally.

816
00:26:45,716 --> 00:26:48,445
Guests who made me flustered...

817
00:26:48,446 --> 00:26:50,385
are the singers we watched...

818
00:26:50,386 --> 00:26:52,356
- while growing up.
- Right.

819
00:26:52,656 --> 00:26:54,456
- They make me super nervous.
- Totally.

820
