836
00:27:30,756 --> 00:27:32,495
What? I see.

837
00:27:32,496 --> 00:27:34,395
I had a senior who sang with the microphone up here.

838
00:27:34,396 --> 00:27:35,625
- You mean him?
- Who sings like that?

839
00:27:35,626 --> 00:27:37,336
- Who can it be?
- Who is it?

840
00:27:37,396 --> 00:27:39,235
- Nobody could make fun of him.
- Who?

841
00:27:39,236 --> 00:27:40,835
- Keep him anonymous.
- But I was older.

842
00:27:40,836 --> 00:27:42,236
Despite being a junior,

843
00:27:42,566 --> 00:27:44,176
- I made fun of that senior.
- Okay.

844
00:27:44,306 --> 00:27:46,646
- That senior got bothered by it.
- Right.

845
00:27:46,976 --> 00:27:48,446
He brought a mic stand.

846
00:27:50,816 --> 00:27:52,746
- Hold on.
- Because his arm kept going up.

847
00:27:52,846 --> 00:27:54,486
- Be the mic stand.
- Here.

848
00:27:54,546 --> 00:27:57,715
Far away, you're my sunshine

849
00:27:57,716 --> 00:27:59,586
We were together

850
00:27:59,686 --> 00:28:00,886
I bet he sang like that.

851
00:28:01,056 --> 00:28:02,455
- No?
- That senior kept flinching.

852
00:28:02,456 --> 00:28:03,595
- Right?
- He kept flinching.

853
00:28:03,596 --> 00:28:05,455
(Bringing the mic up is too passive.)

854
00:28:05,456 --> 00:28:07,565
(I'll move under the mic.)

855
00:28:07,566 --> 00:28:10,396
- Didn't he sing like this?
- Nice.

856
00:28:10,566 --> 00:28:12,195
- I wonder who it is.
- Same.

857
00:28:12,196 --> 00:28:13,305
The song is by Buzz.

858
00:28:13,306 --> 00:28:15,106
- He's anonymous.
- Anonymous.

859
00:28:15,266 --> 00:28:17,105
- I have no idea who it is.
- That reminded me of him.

860
00:28:17,106 --> 00:28:19,106
- He was one of my guests.
- I have no clue.

861
00:28:19,276 --> 00:28:20,876
Kim Yon Ja came on my show.

862
00:28:21,006 --> 00:28:23,745
I learned her moves by watching her in person.

863
00:28:23,746 --> 00:28:24,945
Kim Yon Ja?

864
00:28:24,946 --> 00:28:26,985
- Yes. "Nice to meet you."
- "Amor Fati."

865
00:28:26,986 --> 00:28:28,186
"Nice to meet you, Shin Young."

866
00:28:28,346 --> 00:28:29,546
- "Here's 'Mercury Lamp.'"
- "Mercury Lamp."

867
00:28:29,646 --> 00:28:33,386
One dim evening road

868
00:28:33,586 --> 00:28:36,056
The mercury lamp bloomed like flowers

869
00:28:36,256 --> 00:28:39,596
The street I walked alone with you

870
00:28:39,826 --> 00:28:43,196
The microphone had itchy feet. It kept moving around.

871
00:28:43,536 --> 00:28:45,435
The microphone was far from her mouth.

872
00:28:45,436 --> 00:28:48,105
Her microphone goes down this far, Shin Young.

873
00:28:48,106 --> 00:28:49,535
- I know.
- It returns from here.

874
00:28:49,536 --> 00:28:52,275
The audience applauds like crazy during "National Singing Contest."

875
00:28:52,276 --> 00:28:53,305
You know...

876
00:28:53,306 --> 00:28:54,345
- "10 Minutes" by Lee Hyo Ri?
- Yes.

877
00:28:54,346 --> 00:28:56,006
In trot, it's "Within 10 Minutes."

878
00:28:56,546 --> 00:28:59,476
Okay, I will believe in you

879
00:28:59,546 --> 00:29:01,685
- I'm serious.
- No way.

880
00:29:01,686 --> 00:29:02,885
You can't even hear her.

881
00:29:02,886 --> 00:29:04,616
- That's...
- You can't even hear the lyrics.

882
00:29:05,216 --> 00:29:07,025
- Listen.
- Look at her having fun.

883
00:29:07,026 --> 00:29:09,186
She's asking the audience to sing with her.

884
00:29:09,286 --> 00:29:10,295
Look.

885
00:29:10,296 --> 00:29:11,695
Okay, I will believe in

886
00:29:11,696 --> 00:29:12,725
(You)

887
00:29:12,726 --> 00:29:14,465
If you only love

888
00:29:14,466 --> 00:29:15,666
(Me)

889
00:29:15,896 --> 00:29:17,696
(Amazing at bringing out reactions)

890
00:29:18,436 --> 00:29:21,106
(Powerful voice even without a microphone)

891
00:29:21,436 --> 00:29:24,406
(The microphone can't stay still.)

892
00:29:24,636 --> 00:29:26,646
- That was great.
- She spins the microphone.

893
00:29:26,976 --> 00:29:28,105
Like this.

894
00:29:28,106 --> 00:29:29,745
You're still amazing.

895
00:29:29,746 --> 00:29:31,115
- Respect.
- That's how it is.

896
00:29:31,116 --> 00:29:33,076
- I love them all.
- Shin Young.

897
00:29:33,386 --> 00:29:35,145
- Shin Young.
- Yes?

898
00:29:35,146 --> 00:29:37,755
You really need to do a one-man show.

899
00:29:37,756 --> 00:29:39,915
- Yes.
- I think so.

900
00:29:39,916 --> 00:29:42,326
- I'm working on it.
- We really need to focus on her.

901
00:29:42,686 --> 00:29:44,925
Stop going after her. She's having a hard time.

902
00:29:44,926 --> 00:29:46,095
She's already tired.

903
00:29:46,096 --> 00:29:48,925
Do you deserve to be tired?

904
00:29:48,926 --> 00:29:50,795
I am sincere. Let's go!

905
00:29:50,796 --> 00:29:53,366
I live for the viewers.

906
00:29:53,736 --> 00:29:55,106
I'm bringing it back up.

907
00:29:55,566 --> 00:29:56,935
Ha Bin.

908
00:29:56,936 --> 00:29:58,305
Ha Bin's nickname says,

909
00:29:58,306 --> 00:30:00,505
"Not a Cat Seller, but a catmedian."

910
00:30:00,506 --> 00:30:01,745
- Yes.
- "Catmedian?"

911
00:30:01,746 --> 00:30:02,975
- The cat?
- Cat?

912
00:30:02,976 --> 00:30:05,015
I'm called...

913
00:30:05,016 --> 00:30:06,345
- the "Cat Seller."
- Yes.

914
00:30:06,346 --> 00:30:08,285
You're nothing without your cats.

915
00:30:08,286 --> 00:30:10,855
No, I'm working hard.

916
00:30:10,856 --> 00:30:12,615
I can learn to be a star today.

917
00:30:12,616 --> 00:30:14,525
- Great.
- I can learn.

918
00:30:14,526 --> 00:30:16,425
And I made the word "catmedian."

919
00:30:16,426 --> 00:30:17,426
- "Catmedian?"
- What's a catmedian?

920
00:30:17,427 --> 00:30:19,825
I'm doing comedy with a cat,

921
00:30:19,826 --> 00:30:21,565
so I made the word.

922
00:30:21,566 --> 00:30:22,966
My real nickname is...

923
00:30:23,496 --> 00:30:24,635
They say you look like Oh Ji Heon.

924
00:30:24,636 --> 00:30:26,635
